---
import ContentLayout from '@/layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { t } from '@/i18n/ui';

const lang = 'en';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Philosophy"
  description="Philosophy and thoughts on martial arts."
  lang={lang}
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: t(lang, 'nav.home'), href: '/en/' },
    { label: t(lang, 'nav.philosophy') },
  ]}
>
  <section class="space-y-8">
    <!-- Philosophy Header Image -->
    <div class="not-prose rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg">
      <img src="/images/cultural/meditation.jpg" alt="Meditation" class="w-full h-48 sm:h-64 object-cover" loading="lazy" />
    </div>

    <div>
      <p>
        Kung Fu is far more than a fighting system. It is a philosophy of life rooted in
        thousands of years of Chinese wisdom. At Pak Shao Lin, we believe that the practice
        of martial arts cultivates not only the body, but also the mind and spirit.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2>The Five Virtues of Wude</h2>
      <p>
        Traditional martial arts ethics are guided by <strong>Wude</strong> (martial virtue),
        which encompasses both moral character and the attitude of the practitioner.
      </p>
      <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-6">
        {[
          { virtue: 'Humility', chinese: '謙虛', desc: 'Recognizing there is always more to learn.' },
          { virtue: 'Respect', chinese: '尊敬', desc: 'Honoring teachers, peers, and the art itself.' },
          { virtue: 'Righteousness', chinese: '義', desc: 'Acting with justice and moral integrity.' },
          { virtue: 'Trust', chinese: '信', desc: 'Being reliable and true to your word.' },
          { virtue: 'Loyalty', chinese: '忠', desc: 'Commitment to your school and lineage.' },
          { virtue: 'Perseverance', chinese: '毅力', desc: 'Enduring hardship and continuing to train.' },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="p-5 bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-light hover:border-gold/30 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
            <p class="text-2xl text-gold-dark mb-1">{item.chinese}</p>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-dark">{item.virtue}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-medium mt-1">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2>Mind, Body, and Spirit</h2>
      <p>
        The goal of Kung Fu training goes beyond physical fitness. Through disciplined practice,
        the student develops mental clarity, emotional balance, and spiritual awareness. The
        journey of a martial artist is one of constant self-improvement and self-discovery.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="not-prose p-6 bg-gold/5 rounded-xl border border-gold/20 text-center">
      <blockquote class="text-lg italic text-gray-dark">
        "The supreme art of war is to subdue the enemy without fighting."
      </blockquote>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-medium mt-2">-- Sun Tzu, The Art of War</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>
